    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-02-29T19:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-02-29T19:00:00-05:00" n="944"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d944">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">393.1163 C and M Alliance/78: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Canton</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Myers</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Canton</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-03-01T08:00:00+08:00"
                            >March 1, 1940—8 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received March 1—6:25 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>20. Reference my 10, February 4, 5 p.m., and 18, February 23, 6 p.m.,<note n="51"
                        xml:id="d944fn51">Neither printed.</note> burning of property at Lungchow.
                    The French Consul at <pb facs="0875" n="867" xml:id="pg_867"/> Lungchow has now
                    informed French Consul here that the Chinese forces had evacuated Lungchow and
                    environs more than 48 hours before the burning of the Christian and Missionary
                    Alliance property on December 23, 1939.</p>
                <p>Continuing representations are being made to Japanese Consul General.</p>
                <p>Repeated to Chungking, Peiping, Hong Kong.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Myers</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
